  ja, cs, fr, pt, pt_BR, da, eu, lv, sk, zh_CN, fr).

0.5.1
=====
- Remove endo-mount-point API.
- Only add sync mount option to devices with no volume.
- Add missing function in the symbols file.
- Use the GIO code for reading mount points in endo-mount.
- Make GIO-Unix an optional dependency.
- Use .desktop filename when creating a new desktop item with
  endo-desktop-item-edit.

0.5.0
=====
The API version of endo has been changed from 0.3 to 1, to make it easier
to bump minor and major version numbers in future releases. To compile
against this version of endo, you have to change endo-0.3 to endo-1 in your
configure file. This backwards-incompatible change has also been used to
remove deprecated APIs or APIs that are now provided by Gtk 2.14 or Glib
2.18.

Removed or incompatibly changed classes/enums/functions:
  - Renamed endo_url_about_dialog_hook() to endo_gtk_url_about_dialog_hook().
  - Endo(Mutual)Binding structures are now private.
  - Removed endo_icon_view_{set,get}_{text,markup,pixbuf}_column().
  - Removed EndoPangoEllipsizeMode and related functions.
  - Removed endo_md5_*() functions and EndoMd5Digest.
  - Removed endo_intern_string() and endo_intern_static_string().
  - Removed EndoEllipsizedLabel has been entirely removed.
  - Removed endo_gtk_object_ref_sink() and
    endo_gtk_radio_action_set_current_value().
  - Removed endo_url_show() and endo_url_show_on_screen().

New classes/functions:
  - EndoJob and EndoSimpleJob for handling threaded/asynchronous jobs.
  - endo_str_is_empty(), endo_str_looks_like_an_uri().

Other changes:
- GIO module for handling URIs that are known by the preferred
  applications framework.
- API documentation has been inlined in the code.
- Various other fixes, cleanups and translation updates.

